  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the effect of iron depletion with phlebotomies on
      blood triglyceride concentration, in subjects with hypertriglyceridemia and iron overload,
      compared with a dietary intervention alone.

      All subjects in this study will follow dietary and lifestyle counseling in a period of 3
      months.

      A randomized group will receive phlebotomies every 3 weeks in this period.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
