  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Hyperferritinemia: &gt; 300µgr/L for male and &gt;200µgr/L for female.

          -  Hypertriglyceridemia: &gt; 200 mg/dL in two determinations after at least ten hours of
             fasting and lipid-lowering diet.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Contraindications for phlebotomy: poor venous access, previous intolerance
             (hypotension or apprehension), heart disease, anemia.

          -  Subjects suffering from acute or chronic disease, including liver disease, diabetes,
             cancer, kidney disease or uncontrolled thyroid disease.

          -  Elevated C reactive protein (CRP) as a parameter of inflammation (&gt;10mg/L).

          -  Alcohol intake: over 30 gr. per day for men and 25 gr. per day for women.

          -  Lipid lowering drugs use.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
